Saturday Manila newspapers quoted Teodoro Benigno, President Corazon Aquinoi's press 
secretary, saying Mrs. Aquino told Swiss lawyers that Ferdinand Marcos will be allowed 
to return to the Philippines so that he can be tried for stealing billions of dollars. 

The Philippine government said it will file criminal charges against former President 
Marcos, claiming he stole up to $10 billion of government funds. Mrs. Aquino, however, 
has previously refused to let Marcos return from exile in Hawaii, citing security concerns. 
Philippine law prohibits trial in absentia.

Swiss lawyers are helping the Philippine government trace money that Marcos allegedly 
placed in Swiss banks.</SUM>

