Thursday night about 30 members of the Filipino-American Movement for a Better 
Philippines held a candlelight vigil outside the Philippine Consulate in Los Angeles in 
support of the military coup attempt unfolding in their homeland. Some of the protesters 
entered the consulate offices and confronted a coalition of four Los Angeles, pro-Aquino 
Filipino groups holding a press conference. After some minutes of shouting between the 
Aquino supporters and the anti-government protesters, the protesters departed and order 
was restored. 

The coup attempt is being led by officers linked to renegade Lt. Col. Gregorio Honasan.

Present at the LA press conference was Andrea Aquino, niece of assassinated Marcos 
opponent Benigno Aquino, Cory Aquino's husband.</SUM>

<SUM
DOCSET="d090"
